Substance

	Philosophy

		-
			The term "substance" may be used as an umbrella term for both matter and energy given
			their interchangeability in certain contexts.

			Substance must be quantified using either matter or energy units, so by default it
			should use energy units.
		-

	Principles

		Enermass

			-
				Substance, when used as an umbrella term for both matter and energy, may also be
				referred to as "enermass".
